{"id":508,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":508,"title":"Frontlets or phylacteries","subtitle":"","short_title":"Frontlets or phylacteries","uri":"/scriptures/bd/frontlets","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/frontlets.t1","order":".000.1323"},[".title","Frontlets or phylacteries"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/frontlets.p1","order":".000.1324"},"Strips of parchment on which were written four passages of scriptures (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/13.1-10,11-16"},"Ex. 13:1–10, 11–16"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/6.5-9"},"Deut. 6:5–9"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/11.13-21"},"11:13–21"],") and that were rolled up and attached to bands of leather worn (as an act of obedience to",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/13.9,16"},"Ex. 13:9, 16"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/6.8"},"Deut. 6:8"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/11.18"},"11:18"],") around the forehead or around the arm. The Jews called them",["span.translit",["span.emphasis","tephillin."]],"The Pharisees wore them broader than other people in order to make them as conspicuous as possible (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/23.5"},"Matt. 23:5"],")."]]],"refs":null}
